author: National Geographic
description:
Paid content for argenx. Join National Geographic photographer Josh Cogan as he sets out on a journey of exploration and perseverance with Joey, a man living with CIDP (chronic inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy). Together, Josh and Joey explore the wild and incredible landscapes of Hawaii and push boundaries, from snorkeling with giant manta rays to hiking through Volcanoes National Park. Learn more about their journey here: https://www.cidptravels.com/.

author: National Geographic
description:
In the stunning Wadi Rum desert of Jordan, travel vlogger and Nat Geo explorer Eva zu Beck visits a Bedouin family to learn about their nomadic lifestyle and culture to help prepare for an unforgettable desert adventure in the Middle East. Her navigation skills are put to the ultimate test when left alone in one of the most unforgiving terrains on the planet to complete an extreme survival challenge: find water....without a map or GPS. To complete this intense Superskilled challenge, Eva must quickly learn the native language and animal handling cues in order to befriend a camel for her desert trek. 

Superskilled with Eva zu Beck | S2, E1
